---
description: Test Milestone Creation + Execution within lens-www
alwaysApply: true
---
Test and Debug by using `agent-browser` with `--session-name lens-www` and going to the URL `http://localhost:3000/project/1043`. The tenant should be "Liam's Tenant" and the project name should be "node-hello-world". Test the entire milestone execution flow (takes around 1 - 2 minutes in total) by:
- Ensure you're on the spec version "v2" in the UI by clicking the "Spec Version" dropdown and selecting "v2" from the list.
- Creating a new milestone version by hitting the "Milestone Version" dropdown, and selecting "Create new version". 
- Input the next logical version from the ones already listed (e.g. if v1, v2, v3 exist, enter v4). 
- This will automatically kickoff roadmap generation.
- After roadmap generation is finished, verify the Milestone Version is selected as the one you created.
- Then, select the Milestone card. This will open with a "Review and Approve" button. Click this to open the Milestone Drawer.
- In the Milestone Drawer, click the "Save, Approve, & Start" button.
- Milestone execution is now kicked off.

Monitor console logs and all network requests.